# Patch 0021 — Privacy Center: a Kavacha Settings pane over Firefox's own
# blocking ledger (ROADMAP Phase 4; ADR 0007).
#
# WHAT: a "Privacy Center" pane in Settings (paneKavachaPrivacy) showing
# what Kavacha's protections have blocked — all time / past 7 days / today
# cards, a per-category weekly breakdown (trackers, tracking cookies,
# fingerprinters, cryptominers, social), an ESTIMATED bandwidth-saved
# figure (blocked events x 35 KB — Firefox counts events, never bytes;
# the label says "estimated"), a "counting since" line, clear-statistics,
# and an Active Protections list (ETP strict / TCP / fingerprinting
# protection / query stripping / GPC / cookie-banner auto-reject) read
# live from prefs so the pane is informative even at zero counts.
#
# DATA: pure reader over protections.sqlite via TrackingDBService
# (sumAllEvents / getEarliestRecordedDate) and PrivacyMetricsService
# (getWeeklyStats / getTodayStats). Nothing new is collected. NOTE:
# PrivacyMetricsService is a MOZ_SRC_FILES module — import it via
# moz-src:///browser/components/protections/..., NOT resource:///modules/
# (the resource URI silently doesn't exist; same trap as patch 0011's
# NewTabPagePreloading).
#
# WIRING: follows Zen's own pane recipe — nav button + #include in
# preferences-xhtml.patch, register_module in preferences-js.patch, script
# via jar-mn.patch. register_module's template-replacement special case is
# extended from startsWith("paneZen") to also match "paneKavacha" (without
# it the pane renders empty under the settings redesign). Palette command
# "Open Privacy Center" (new PRIVACY domain) in KavachaCommandRegistry.
#
# Verified via Marionette 2026-07-15: seeded protections.sqlite with known
# per-category counts (same INSERT the protections tests use), opened the
# pane through the palette command, and read back exact card/breakdown
# values, bandwidth math, "counting since", posture all-On, and
# clear-statistics zeroing the ledger. Meta-patch edits validated with
# git apply --check against pristine Firefox 152.0.6 files.
